<h1 > CTG Pipelines </h1>
<br>
    <h3 id="ctg-samplesheet-guide">CTG SampleSheet guide</h3>
    <h4 style=text-align:left id="_how-to-set-up-samplesheets-for-successful-automation-of-transfer-and-analysis-at-ctg_"><em>How to set up samplesheets for successful automation of transfer and analysis at CTG</em></h4>
    <br>
    <br>
    <h2 id="Main steps">Main steps</h2>
    <p style=font-size:20px> 1. Automatic transfer: Name samplesheet in runfolder with prefix "<strong>CTG_SampleSheet.</strong>" </p>
    <p style=font-size:20px> 2. Automatic pipeline execution: Describe which pipeline after prefix: "CTG_SampleSheet.<strong>name-of-pipeline</strong>.csv". See "Samplesheet name" in table below.</p>
    <p style=font-size:20px> 3. Every pipeline has specific requirements for samplesheet format and content. Click pipelines in table below for more details for the specific pipeline </p>
    <br>
    <p style=font-size:20px> <strong>General</strong>: Sample_ID and Sample_Name can ONLY contain "_" as a special character. All other special characters will cause demux to crash</p>

<h4> Usage </h4>
<ul style=font-size:13px>
  <li> 'Pipeline' to go to github page for pipeline (description of input files)</li>
  <li> 'QC' to list all project QC for given pipeline </li>
  <li> 'Samplesheet name' to copy samplesheet name to clipboard  </li>
</ul>

